      • close

        public void close()
        Flushes any pending statements, commits transaction, and closes this dataset instance. Note that the underlying JDBC statements may remain open since they may be shared with other graphs.

        It is the responsibility of the caller to createFrom to close this instance after use.

        Specified by:

      • createFrom

        public static DatasetGraphOracleHybrid createFrom(GraphOracleSem gos,
                                                  org.apache.jena.sparql.core.DatasetGraph dgThirdParty,
                                                  boolean bPopulateWithDbData,
                                                  int iDopForSqlRead,
                                                  long lMaxQuadsAllowed)
                                           throws java.sql.SQLException
        This static method returns an instance of DatasetGraphOracleHybrid based on the metadata associated with the GraphOracleSem passed as the argument.

        Both the DatasetGraphOracleHybrid object returned and the GraphOracleSem object, gos, passed as the argument will share the same JDBC connection, JDBC and SQL settings, and underlying Oracle RDF model, attachment, and model settings. This means that any commits performed in one object will also commit changes made in the other object.

        Although both objects share the same resources, closing one object will not close the other. To ensure proper closing of the shared JDBC connection and freeing of shared resources, close both the DatasetGraphOracleHybrid object and GraphOracleSem object after use.

        Note that the GraphOracleSem object pass as an argument, gos, does not need to remain open to use the DatasetGraphOracleHybrid object returned by this method. It is a good practice to close the gos object after the DatasetGraphOracleHybrid object is instantiated.

        The GraphOracleSem object, gos, must not be null.

        Parameters:
        gos - GraphOracleSem object on which to base the new DatasetGraphOracleHybrid instance.
        dgThirdParty -
        bPopulateWithDbData -
        iDopForSqlRead -
        lMaxQuadsAllowed -
        Returns:
        DatasetGraphOracleHybrid object based on the same underlying model as gos and sharing the same resources as gos.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - SQL exception object.
